  "body": "Link: https://docs.perl6.org/language/functions#index-entry-MAIN\r\nit says that you pass named para both `-v` or `--verbose`\r\nsure the Usage message is: `main.p6 -v|--verbose=<Any>`\r\nbut it also works by `perl6 main.p6 -verbose=1 ` and `perl6 main.p6 --v=1 `\r\nthe program below\r\n\r\nsub MAIN(:v(:$verbose) is required) {\r\n  say $verbose;\r\n  say \"Accepted!\";\r\n}\r\n\r\nso is it a bug, or just a missing doc?\r\n\r\n@unclechu\r\n@moritz\r\n\r\nsince i see your talk in https://irclog.perlgeek.de/perl6/2017-09-24#i_15209949",
